# Defense-in-depth — files that historically tend to contain credentials.
# Note: this does NOT replace a proper secrets manager. Never store live
# tokens in a file even with gitignore; use Windows Credential Manager (see
# SECURITY.md, "Provisioning a GitHub PAT" section).
